<header class="bg-gray-900 text-white">
  <div
    class="mx-auto max-w-screen-xl px-4 py-32 lg:flex lg:h-screen lg:items-center"
  >
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl text-center">
      <h1
        class="py-2 bg-gradient-to-r from-green-300 via-blue-500 to-purple-600 bg-clip-text text-3xl font-extrabold text-transparent md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl 2xl:text-8xl"
      >
        <span>Social Sentiment during the Energy Crisis: </span>
        <span class="sm:block">Analyzing Human-Machine Agreement</span>
      </h1>

      <p class="mx-auto py-4 max-w-4xl md:text-xl leading-relaxed">
        Our research interest is to analyze the agreement of text classification
        between human annotators and large language models (LLM) questioned
        through prompting. Thus, your task in the survey is annotating Tweets in
        terms of their topic and sentiment. In addition, we encourage you to
        provide us with selected socio-demographic features. We will utilize
        these to analyze if the LLM's response resembles the opinion of specific
        groups.
      </p>

      <div class="py-8 flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-4">
        <button
          class="block w-full rounded border border-blue-600 bg-blue-600 px-12 py-3 font-medium text-white hover:bg-transparent hover:text-white focus:outline-none focus:ring active:text-opacity-75 sm:w-auto"
          id="startSurvey"
        >
          Start Survey
        </button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</header>

<script>
  const button = document.getElementById("startSurvey");

  if (button != null) {
    button.addEventListener("click", () => {
      window.scrollTo({
        top: window.innerHeight,
        left: 0,
        behavior: "smooth",
      });
    });
  }
</script>
